{{Infobox Organization |name = Association of Speakers Clubs |image = ASC-logo-basic.jpg |abbreviation = ASC |motto = "Achieving Speaking Confidence" |status = Non-profit organization |purpose = Educational |membership = over 1000 members; over 100 clubs |website = [http://www.the-asc.org.uk/] }}
The '''Association of Speakers Clubs''' ('''ASC''') is a [[Great Britain|British]] confederation of about 150 clubs around the country that promote the skill of [[public speaking]].
==History== The ASC was formed by de-merger from [[Toastmasters International|Toastmasters International (TI)]] in 1973. Most of the TI clubs in [[Scotland]] and northern and central [[England]] joined the ASC.
==External links== *{{Official website|http://www.speakersclubs.uk}} *[http://www.speakerstrust.org Speakers Trust]
